<br>
Shaman mobs always did put minor buffs and SoW on their ally mobs. In making casters smarter I'd expect them to not only use more damaging spells but to fully buff like players too. <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133603><img src=http://members.aol.com/_ht_a/jayrj1/sigsjoc.jpg><br>My Profile</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 405<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/7/02 1:28:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caster AI changes</span><hr size=1> Instead of just avoiding caster mobs, I'd encourage people to try new tactics.  If the mobs are buffing themselves, get out the debuffs.  If their nukes are nasty now, have your stuns memmed and ready.  Paladins are probably one of the best suited classes in terms of having tools in our arsenal to handle these changes.<br>
<br>
Long before this change, I had a lot of success fighting the Sirens in SG.  The first time I went, I was puller and MT for the group.  Then a higher level SK showed up and wanted to take over as puller and tank.  He started pulling, but would often be charmed by the time he got the mob back to the group, and would often get charmed during the fight.  This hadn't happened the whole time I had been pulling and tanking (with my stuns, they hardly ever got a spell off, not to mention no problems with aggro control), and I started getting tells from the other group members asking me to take over pulling again.<br>
<br>
That was one example of a camp many people avoid or only go to in force, because of nasty caster mobs.  If more places are like this now, it just makes more places well suited to having a Paladin as your puller/main tank. <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a>
