i say keep the changes but either take some more hp/ac/atk from casters, or just increase the exp they give. Id love it to be more challenging as long as I get the same amount of exp because we all know exp is a time drain already =) <p><img src="http://webhome.idirect.com/~peterp/EQ/bastovbg.jpg" border=0></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukysharn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kysharn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/10/02 1:32:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Caster AI changes</span><hr size=1> It definitely makes things interesting now.  Two types of encounters that are much more interesting and much more difficult to &quot;plan&quot; an attack on.<br>
<br>
1. Deep Cavern Lotus- DD attacks, Entombment of ice, Wrath of the Gods. Between all that it was difficult for the cleric to know when to heal a bard friend.  When I took the Bards place it went much smoother. When we added another paladin, it was smooth as glass.<br>
<br>
2. Atulus' in Akheva- Tashania, Charm, Mez, Anarchy, Immobilize, Grav Flux. These make the encounters much more interesting and when grouped without a mana battery of any sort it's very very fun, and makes you very mana concious.<br>
<br>
 Overall I like the changes so far. It makes encounters more than a mindless grind. It seems to have the added effect of slowing solo classes from taking huge camps, for better or worse. <p><br>
Kysharn
